## What this slice does
Stamps attributes.integration on the op-wrapping ("settings.op_settings") family.
Each integration's get_<vendor>_patcher now derives its base via
with_integration_metadata(settings.op_settings, <VENDOR>_INTEGRATION); every op
built from that base via model_copy inherits the metadata. One module-level
constant + one base-line change per file. Bedrock is special (it calls weave.op
directly, not via OpSettings), so each of its 5 op sites gets
attributes=BEDROCK_INTEGRATION.as_attributes().

## Distribution names (meta.package_version source)
Passed distribution_name where the PyPI name differs from the integration name:
mistral->mistralai, cerebras->cerebras-cloud-sdk, google_genai->google-genai,
vertexai->google-cloud-aiplatform, huggingface->huggingface-hub,
langchain_nvidia_ai_endpoints->langchain-nvidia-ai-endpoints,
autogen->autogen-agentchat, bedrock->boto3. Others default to the integration name.
resolve_package_version is guarded (missing package -> version omitted, never raises).

## How it was built
Family A edits were fanned out to parallel subagents with a strict 3-part recipe
(import, module constant, route base through with_integration_metadata); diffs were
reviewed centrally. verifiers kept its `base: OpSettings` annotation; autogen kept
its `base_settings` name + indentation; google_genai has no patcher global so the
constant sits after imports.

